title: Google, Facebook and Twitter threaten to leave Pakistan over censorship law
text: Global internet companies Facebook, Google and Twitter and others have banded together and threatened to leave Pakistan after the South Asian nation granted blanket powers to local regulators to censor digital content. title: Apple hits Facebook over ad-targeting practices
text: Apple iOS users will have the choice of whether apps can track them for ad purchases and will limit the sale of information from those apps to data brokers. CNBC's Josh Lipton reports on how Apple's decision is fueling the privacy war with Facebook.

title: Apple and Facebook feud over who's violating your privacy more
text: Apple's privacy chief is accusing Facebook of collecting "as much data as possible."

title: Zuckerberg Says He Doesn't Want Facebook to Be Addictive
text: Nov.20 -- Facebook Chief Executive Officer Mark Zuckerberg tells Senators he doesn't want his product to be addictive. He spoke on Nov. 17 before the Senate Judiciary Committee about content moderation and Facebook's role in political discourse.

title: Apple accuses Facebook of 'disregard for user privacy'
text: Criticism made as Apple pushes ahead with transparency feature disliked by advertisers

title: EU digital chief, tech giants call on new rules rescheduled to Dec. 2
text: A video call between the European Union's digital chief and Alphabet, Apple, Amazon and Facebook to discuss draft rules to curb their powers has been postponed until Dec. 2, an EU official said on Friday.

title: Apple and Facebook are at each other's throats over who exploits user data more
text: Apple and Facebook traded barbs this week over which one of them exploits their users more. Apple struck the first blow on Thursday in a letter addressed to nonprofits, including Human Rights Watch and the Electronic Frontier Foundation, saying it doesn't hoover up detailed user data to sell to third parties. Facebook takes a "very different approach," Apple said.

title: Facebook Faces The Ax In Billion-Dollar Market Vietnam: Report
text: Facebook Inc's (NASDAQ: FB) operations in Vietnam face a shut down unless the social networking company complies with enhanced censorship requirements, Reuters reported Thursday.  What Happened: An official of the Mark Zuckerberg-led company said the Vietnamese government told the company to increase the volume of content it already restricts in the Southeast Asian country but it refused to comply, according to Reuters.
